Date: Wed, 20 Nov 2024 19:20:30 +0100
Subject: [PATCH] UPnP: Subscribe socket is closed on LAN change Problem:
 Change on LAN interface causes restart of miniupnpd to update config Restart
 of miniupnpd loses every subscribe request Cause: Miniupnpd get every LAN
 information during init. If LAN is changed, miniupnpd needs to be restarted
 Solution: Change SIGUSR1 to reload LAN infos as well as WAN infos Issue:
 [CDROUTER][UPnP] ConnectionStatus value in NOTIFY event is NOT correctly
 updated after WAN connectivity Loss [change]
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

References: PCF-1833, FEAT-13

Signed-off-by: Théo-Paul Bodin <theo-paul.bodin@softathome.com>
